< Name>
Ryan Payne</Name>
<time>1534429225577<//time>< Rating>
4</Rating>
< review>
This place felt pretty average to me and it had some ups and downs.

The good: Good location right in downtown Petaluma. Reasonable prices, seemed like they have good lunch specials and happy hour specials and such. Relaxed atmosphere. Huge sushi menu and the sushi we had was pretty good.

The bad: Service was pretty slow and we had to remind staff what was in our sushi order. The non-sushi menu items we had were okay but not anything to write home about. I was especially excited about the curry and it was disappointing. The sauce was reasonably tasty but they only served a tiny little bit of it, not even enough to cover the meat let alone the rice.

All said, we were satisfied and I'd go there again. Can definitely recommend if you want something more convenient and good value and less fancy. But I'd probably recommend only ordering sushi.< /review>

<date>1574380278476< /date><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
Almost two weeks ago I met someone special and we shared our first meal here. It was a delightful, above-average dining experience on all counts. The sushi and tempura were delicious, the service no-nonsense, and the ambiance for the time of day (lunch on a Saturday in mid-autumn) was peaceful. It was the perfect setting to get comfortable for a 3+ hours long leisurely meal steeped in meaningful conversation. I'm certain I will be returning with her, since it's one of her favorite spots to eat in Petaluma. This was my first visit and I'm certain it won't be my last.</review>

I would have loved to give this more stars, it had a great staff and location but the food was so below average. The tempura used was so gross and cheap. As pictured you can see it's the cheap mix you buy at any local market and overly watered down. Flavors were off and did not taste fresh. I honestly would not come here again especially since the prices were about average, when it had the taste of a cheap college town sushi shop. If you want good sushi try something else. < Review>
I feel confident that I received a fair deal on our Tesla and the staff was exemplary during our visit.  Enterprise is known for their customer service and the staff in Huntington Beach did not disappoint.  There is a mountain of paperwork but we moved through it pretty rapidly and they even picked up a knosh for us while we were waiting.  The only hard part with Enterprise Car Sales is that you have to pay to transport the vehicle before you get to see it in person so you are out the transfer fee before you get a face to face look at the car, especially the exterior paint.  As former rental cars for Enterprise you are purchasing the car "As Is," and there are little nicks and chips on the exterior paint from being a rental so that is hard to see on photos before you pay the transport fee.  After purchasing our vehicle, we had to have the exterior trunk repainted and that was a pretty good chunk that was not covered by Enterprise but we are still content with the deal we received.<//Review>

< Review>
There are a lot of coffee shops in Encinitas to choose from, but Surfdog's is by far my favorite! Laid back atmosphere with friendly staff that really embodies the vibe of Encinitas. They have a great assortment of muffins, bagels, and smoothies to choose from. And most importantly, the coffee is top-notch. Definitely swing by if you're in the area and need a cup of Joe.</Review>

<UserId.>118417939282901838818<//UserId.><name>Wan ker<//name>< Date>
1543807209432<//Date>
<Rate>2< /Rate>< review>
VERY POOR SERVICE! We haven't stopped by here for lunch in ages while on our Sunday bike rides on the 101. And that was because when we buy a couple of lattes we also want something to eat and they had been out of bagels as early as midday on occasions. So even though the lattes were pretty decent we got sick of stopping and finding out they had no food. We haven't bothered to stop by here in quite a few months because there are more reliable options close by. My wife and I decided to take a punt while having a late bike ride today and called in here at 1.45pm to find they had some bagels in the glass display cabinet. I spoke with a dude behind the counter about how many shots are usually used in their mugs. He kind of gave me a blank stare while holding up a mug. I asked about what milk they had available and he replied non fat and while milk. We wanted 2%. Most thinking baristas these days know they can conjure 2% fat milk by blending non fat and whole milk. I had to ask this guy can he do that? He replied that because of his self proclaimed math prowess that it should be a cinch. So I ordered 2 one shot lattes with hazelnut syrup and a Pipeline Bagel. After a few minutes we collected our lattes at the counter and sat down to drink them while we waited for our bagel. Things did seem a bit out of whack because normally when we have ordered here before the person would take payment before processing our order. We were sitting there drinking our lattes which tasted terrible .....like frothy milk and we had to ask for more hazelnut syrup. After about 15 minutes I thought where is our bagel order? I asked the math genius behind the counter and daaaaah he forgot to tell the other worker to make our lunch order. My wife then went to the counter as he requested to make our payment. Sitting there with our getting colder lousy lattes we finally got our Pipeline Bagel at 2.22pm which was 30 minutes after I ordered it. Soon after the dude brought our order to our table he disappeared out the front door obviously gone for the day. Needless to say we will never be coming back because bad service really sucks!<//review>

<userid>112759605020826498844</userid><review>Marlene (sp?) gave me the worst beard trim and line up I have ever received. Bar none. Read the wonderful reviews so thought I'd give them a try. The place has that old school barber shop feel that I love and takes me back to when I used to go with my Dad every weekend. Anyway, I digress. Came in at 5 on a Saturday for next available, explaining I needed a lineup and for my sideburns to be blended. No change in length, no crazy requests.

She began by asking me how I wanted my hair cut. I explained I wasn't there for a haircut, just the beard lineup. She asked if I was sure, because she specializes in long hair. I reiterated that I was certain. Now, most barber shops make you feel good about going in. They lather your face, straight razor, hot towel, all the while maintaining a poise and confidence that tells you they've done this a thousand times a day. This, is not what I received. My barber was very uncertain, alternating between clippers, electric razor and scissors on my cheek alone. I was spun in that chair more times than a ride at Disney with the kids. I lost faith in this shop more and more as this continued.

What I left with was an uneven beard line, beard trimmed in places I didn't ask for, my neck cut in three places (she explained it was because my hair was thick; she didn't even give/offer/ask about a straight razor, just used her electric razor) and the rest of my face feeling raw. She was going to go back over my neck again, but I politely declined as my neck was already bleeding and that electric razor was not her ally.

Three days later, with my uneven lengths, uneven sides and cuts-still-healing- beard, I've gone ahead and just shaved it off to start new because no barbershop on earth could fix the fact that I look like if Abraham Lincoln's beard had been cut by an intoxicated Edward Scissorhands. Biggest regret? Not learning price until she charged me $26 for something my niece could've done better blindfolded.<//review><Rate>1< /Rate><user_name>Erik Weatherford</user_name><Pictures>None</Pictures>< Gmap_id>

< username>
Gabrielle Santiago< /username>
<date>1462813745068</date>< rating>
5< /rating>
< review>
Yonkers Cafe is a cute little cafe serving wine, coffee, and sandwiches. It's located in the same vicinity as Toyose and Devil's Teeth but you would never know that it was there unless you walked in. The owners had samples of essentially all their sandwich specials during our event so I was lucky enough to try them all. The Yonkers special is probably my favorite one. It's perfect if you wanted to pick something up to snack on at the beach due to its close proximity. By no means are the sandwiches huge or cheap, but for what it's worth they're piled high and are very delicious. They have a pretty decent wine selections as well. Only got to tried the chardonnay and the rose, but thought it was awesome that they offered wine/beer on top of the fact that they serve bomb sandwiches.

It's a small place but they do have a tv playing whatever game is on, free wifi, and a clean bathroom! All in all, this place makes for a great detour if you happen to be in the area!</review>

<Review>Great neighborhood place, staff is fantastic, really good prices< /Review><pics>None</pics><resp>None</resp>< gmapID>
0x8085878f7548a5ff:0x520256ec8454951< /gmapID>
</record></dataset><record>
<Rating>5< /Rating><name>AJ Cartas< /name>< time>
1458165987555<//time>
< GmapID>
0x8085878f7548a5ff:0x520256ec8454951< /GmapID>
<review>Yonkers Cafe replaced Sea Biscuit Cafe & Wine Bar, which apparently is a spot where numerous stores have been built and destroyed. After coming here, I can confidently say that the only time Yonkers Cafe will move out is because of the lack of space that it could accommodate its customers.

TL;DR version:

1. Good food - get the Yonkers special
2. Great customer service
3. I endorse Yonkers Cafe

ATMOSPHERE:
This cafe is relatively small. If I could guess the maximum capacity, I would put it between 15-20. Once you enter the cafe, I would say that the vibe is a mood booster. There are booth chairs and booths inside with Wi-Fi so you could do work here! On the side near the door, there are stacks of cups and a container filled with water for self-serve.

FOOD & DRINKS:
The sandwich that I got was the Yonkers Special, which had pastrami inside of the ciabatta bun. Honestly, I didn't know what pastrami was until my boyfriend told me that it was splendid and that I should try it. Best decision of the day! The Yonkers Special was incredibly flavorful. I requested to have "everything" included. Each ingredient perfectly complemented each other from every bite. I thought I was going to get full from eating the whole sandwich, but in fact, I was still craving more!

I tried both their hot and iced coffee which was probably one of the best coffee I've ever tried. I'm not a huge coffee drinker, but I'm down to get some from Yonkers.

CUSTOMER SERVICE:
The definition of superlative customer service can be found here. As soon as I walked in, I was immediately greeted by employees here as if I was visiting a friend. I don't know about you, but when employees are smiling when they take my order, it gives me a positive vibe, and the chances of me coming back are higher.

One thing that stood out to me for the duration of my visit at Yonkers was Devil's Teeth Baking Company, who I would say is their competitor on Noriega Street because of the proximity. Let me tell you that Devil's Teeth has nothing on Yonkers. Yes, their breakfast sandwich may be tasty, but Yonkers hands down beats Devil's in the atmosphere of their respective restaurants, food & drinks, and most definitely in customer service. Devil's Teeth's customer service is non-existent. I remember my first visit and that's an ever-lasting impression on a consumer.

Would I come back here? Yes! Would I recommend this to friends? Hell yes!

My name is AJ Cartas and I approve of this business.</review><pictures>None<//pictures>< response>
None<//response>

We will never use this place again! My son needed his car towed 2 blocks from the house because it was inoperable..ez tow is less about 3 or 4 blocks from our house as well..they told us it would be about 45 min b4 arrival..after a hour and 15 min we called and they said oh he will be there in 12 min..ok still no tech after half hour..we called again got hung up on...called again...finally the guy shows up..hes here for 5 min loads the car on the tow truck and charges us a whopping $300!!! < text>
I had a problem with a brand new Whirlpool refrigerator I purchased through Home Depot. Whirlpool coordinated a repair with Appliance Repair Specialist. I cannot speak about the cost of the repair since my repair was under warranty but I was extremely happy with the service!

Francisco, the repair specialist who was assigned to me, is skilled, friendly, and pro-active. He was very empathetic and understood how awful it is to have a non-working brand new refrigerator especially during COVID-19. During his first visit, he took time to inspect all the possible damages on the fridge and once he found out what's the most likely cause, he did his best to secure the parts and earliest time slot so that we don't have to wait too long. I am very satisfied with his service and though we would prefer not to have problems with our fridge anymore, I would definitely request him again if problems show up again.

Francisco also wore his face mask, gloves, and shoe coverings the whole time while he was at our residence.<//text>

He checked the refrigerator on 1/11/2020 and said that THE REFRIGERANT WAS COMPLETELY GONE! This company was contacted via the home improvement store that sold us the freezer and with the unit being broken under the warranty time, they pick the repair company.

<Review>I contacted Appliance Repair Specialists through the Kitchenaid website.  My refrigerator was not cooling properly.  Their response to my website service request was very quick and they were able to send our a Technician within a few days.  I was very happy about the response time.

The Technician who showed up did not seem that familiar with refrigerators/refrigeration.  As soon as he walked in the door he was on the phone talking with another Technician and describing my issue to them.  it was pretty clear he was simply following their recommendation, and not diagnosing the issue himself.  The technician on the phone told him it was likely the coils were dirty and needed to be cleaned.  I didn't think that was the issue, but I had a feeling his experience wasn't going to allow him to diagnose something deeper than that.  Sure enough, after he left the problem returned.

I called Appliance Repair Specialists back and let them know my issue was not resolved.  They initially said the same Technician would need to come back out to finish the job.  I explained that I was concerned about his level of expertise, but they said it was policy of one Technician to finish the job he started.   I was disappointed, but figured  I would keep going down this path.  Fortunately they called back within a few minutes and let me know they would be sending out a sealed system Specialist instead of the original Technician.  He would be back out to my home in two days.  Again, I thought that was great response time.

Alejandro was the Specialist that showed up, and he clearly knew what he was doing.  He showed up with replacement thermistors and said they were typically the part that caused my issue.  I was pleasantly surprised he was aware of the issue before arriving and had parts with him to try and resolve it.  He replaced the parts and said that if they did not resolve the issue it would most definitely be the circuit board.  Unfortunately the replaced themistors did not correct the issue, so I found a replacement circuit board online and installed it myself (it was a simple plug and play operation).  It's been a few days and the refrigerator has been cooling fine.  Alejandro's diagnosis was 100% correct.

I'm very happy with the response I received to my requests, and everyone was great to work with.  I just wish a more experienced Technician had been sent out the first time and perhaps we could have avoided the additional visit and time it took to fix the issue.<//Review>< Pics>
None< /Pics>

<text>Sheryl Heidt is the best speech pathologist I have had worked with.  She does an amazing job with children and adults.

I worked in the public school system for 23 years and observed numerous speech pathologists in a school setting.  Often times, students were put in small groups with an aide to do the therapy.  At Effective Speech Therapy, Sheryl works one on one with her client.

Our granddaughter had severe apraxia of speech which is a motor planning deficit.  She was 85% unintelligible throughout kindergarten.  She desperately wanted to play with other children, but was unable to even speak her name and had to have it written on a paper to introduce herself.  Sheryl worked tirelessly with our granddaughter.  We had scheduled appointments and she notified us immediately if there was a cancellation so that we could get additional treatments.  Therapy started and finished on time; no time was wasted in a waiting room.

Sheryl is a phenomenal diagnostician and treatment was adjusted throughout our granddaughter's therapy sessions to help her meet her full potential. Sheryl worked on motor skills with her regarding mouth and tongue formation, air movement in the mouth and nose, and the pitch and volume she used when speaking.  Sheryl also worked on social cues and the ability to read body language and interact with other children and adults.

Sheryl has a wealth of knowledge and a variety of interventions to use.  I was able to talk with her about the previous week's challenges and she was able to weave that information into the therapy session.  As a result, our granddaughter has finished fourth grade and is one of the top readers in her class.  She had read the series of books titled "A Series of Unfortunate Events;" books rich in vocabulary.  She even earned the first place reading ribbon in her class.  Our granddaughter is social and loves to talk and interact with other children.  Without Sheryl's intervention our granddaughter would have been lost in a public school setting.

Sheryl has also worked with my husband who has an atypical parkinsonism; a diagnosis that leads to speech, language, and cognitive difficulties.  My husband's physician at UCLA has been extremely pleased with the progress he has made with Sheryl.  She has helped him to be able to access his prior language skills using theories of neuroplasticity and the creation of new neural pathways.  She has helped us, as a family, to find ways to communicate with my husband to reduce the stress on him.  She has given him tools to help deal with public situations. Sheryl is not the type of speech pathologist who will open a book to page 33 and next week, you will go to page 34.  She is constantly listening and interacting with you, reassessing and encouraging you.  With her help, my husband's quality of life has been greatly improved.

There are not enough words to describe what a phenomenal speech pathologist Sheryl Heidt is and the lasting impact she has had on our family.  We would highly recommend her for all your speech and language problems.< /text>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>
< resp>
None<//resp>

I called the appliance company again who services Whirlpool refrigerators and when Raymond came in to see what was wrong,  he was perplexed within 48 hours the refrigerator is frosting over again, his response was...to order a door which would take another 6-8 weeks to order the door, he said maybe that could be the problem and admits the temperature part did not fix the issue. < Text>
Technician misdiagnosed the problem with my washing machine and won't refund me the diagnostic fee of $85 I paid. My 3 year old Maytag washing machine started giving me an error code of F51. I called and scheduled an appointment for repair. The technician named Andrew arrived on 9/28/13. He diagnosed the machine as needing a new rps sensor kit. He said he would have to order the part on Monday. I paid the $85 diagnostic fee and told him I would let him know Monday if I would go ahead with the repair. He told me either way he was ordering the part because these go out all the time. He emailed me an invoice for $195.74 for the repair to be completed not including the $85 I already paid for the diagnosis. Monday morning 9/30/13 at 8am I called back to let them know that I would go ahead and move forward with the repair, there was no answer. I called back at 10am and asked when they could come back to repair the machine. The girl said she didn't know, but she would call me back and let me know. By 4pm Monday I still have heard nothing. I start looking for another repairmen. I found a number for Quality Appliance Repair Services. The owner, Mike answers and I tell him the diagnosis from Appliance Repair Specialists. He picks up the rps sensor kit locally and is at my house by 5pm. He lifts the machine tightens a bolt that came loose, ran the machine and it works fine no more F51. He told me he's never had to replace and rps sensor on a Maytag. I call Appliance repair Specialists and speak to Erica about a refund for $85 I paid because it was not diagnosed properly. She says that her supervisor is on vacation and won't know anything until they get back. She goes on to say that there's no way I will get a refund because the technician did his job. I believe if he did his job it would have been fixed 9/28/13, when he came out. I feel completely ripped off by this company and don't know how they are in business treating people this way.<//Text>
